Blurb::
Pointers to methods to execute sequantially or collaboratively
Description::
\c method_pointer_list specifies by name the methods that are to be executed by
a \c hybrid \c sequential or \c hybrid \c collaborative method. Its argument is 
a list of strings that refer to method blocks by name (i.e. to their 
\ref method-id_method labels).
